The paper discusses sub-Nyquist radar systems which use compressed sensing (CS) methods for signal recovery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory) which deals with the mathematical foundations of CS. The paper also discusses the use of sub-Nyquist processing for estimating target locations, which falls under cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.SP (Statistics Theory). The paper also discusses the use of multiple-input-multiple-output array radars, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the application of sub-Nyquist and cognitive radars to imaging systems such as synthetic aperture radar, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
